 <center><article>
	<center><h2>how to make perfect biryani</h2></center>
	<center><p>2021-12-13</p></center>
	<center><p>Making perfect biryani hinges on quality basmati rice, properly marinated protein, fragrant spices, and the dum cooking technique—a slow, sealed steam that melds flavors.  The key is balancing components: rice cooked to 70% doneness, richly spiced meat, crispy fried onions (birista), and aromatic layers enhanced with saffron, ghee, and fresh herbs. </p></center>
	<center><img src="https://imgs.search.brave.com/woU-5pgOMeQouiQI9ZZeZm3vDiD-88xk9WznldBPsjw/rs:fit:860:0:0:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdGF0/aWMudmVjdGVlenku/Y29tL3N5c3RlbS9y/ZXNvdXJjZXMvdGh1/bWJuYWlscy8wNDUv/NDc3LzE3NS9zbWFs/bC9leHBsb3Jpbmct/dGhlLWZsYXZvcnMt/b2YtYXV0aGVudGlj/LXBha2lzdGFuaS1j/dWlzaW5lLWJpcnlh/bmkta29mdGEta2Vi/YWItbGFzc2ktc2Ft/b3NhLWphbGViaS1h/aS1nZW5lcmF0aXZl/LWZyZWUtcGhvdG8u/anBn" width="" height="" border="0" alt=""></center>
	<center><a href="https://www.indianhealthyrecipes.com/chicken-biryani-recipe/">read more</a></center>
 </article></center>
 <center><article>
	<center><h2>how to make palak panner</h2></center>
	<center><p>2021-12-14</p></center>
	<center><p>Palak Paneer is a classic North Indian dish made with creamy spinach puree and soft paneer cubes, flavored with aromatic spices.  The key to a rich, vibrant Palak Paneer lies in blanching the spinach to preserve its color and using freshly ground spices for depth of flavor.  While traditionally made with cream, you can easily create a lighter version using milk or yogurt</p></center>
	<center><img src="https://imgs.search.brave.com/UsiSPKnfbhixRFxEUgKsBmb5hC8mDKeVaI4I_r7oRz4/rs:fit:500:0:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu/bXVuYXR5Y29va2lu/Zy5jb20vd3AtY29u/dGVudC91cGxvYWRz/LzIwMjIvMDkvbWFr/aW5nLXBhbGFrLXBh/bmVlci1zdGVwLTEy/LW1vZGktNzIweDQw/NS5qcGc" width="" height="" border="0" alt=""></center>
	<center><a href="https://www.indianhealthyrecipes.com/palak-paneer-recipe-easy-paneer-recipes-step-by-step-pics/">read more</a></center>
 </article></center>
 <center><article>
	<center><h2>how to make daal makkhani</h2></center>
	<center><p>2021-12-17</p></center>
	<center><p>To make authentic Dal Makhani, start by soaking 1 cup of whole black urad dal (black gram) and ¼ cup of kidney beans (rajma) overnight for at least 8 hours.  Drain the lentils, rinse them, and pressure cook them with water, whole spices like black cardamom, bay leaves, and cinnamon, until they are completely soft and can be easily mashed</p></center>
	<center><img src="https://imgs.search.brave.com/NYZ-gOKiP6SsOyqqzhGOET5e1-mofLJcmcMx9nHM_00/rs:fit:500:0:1:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9jZG4u/dGFybGFkYWxhbC5j/b20vbWVkaWEvcmVj/aXBlL21ldGhvZC8y/MDI1LzAxLzE2L0Rh/bF9tYWtoYW5pX0RT/QzI2NTUud2VicD93/PTgwMCZmb3JtYXQ9/d2VicA" width="" height="" border="0" alt=""></center>
	<center><a href="https://www.indianhealthyrecipes.com/dal-makhani-recipe/">read more</a></center>
 </article></center>
 
 
 <article>
	<ul>
		<li>Paneer – 250g, cubed</li>
		<li>Cornflour – 3–4 tbsp
</li>		<li>Salt – to taste
</li>
		<li>Kashmiri red chili powder – ½ tsp (for color)
</li>		<li>Oil – for frying and sautéing
</li>
		<li>Ginger – 1-inch, minced
</li>		<li>Garlic – 4–5 cloves, minced
</li>
		<li>Green chilies – 2–3, slit
</li>
	</ul>
	<ol>
		<li>Prepare the paneer coating: In a bowl, mix cornflour, all-purpose flour, salt, and Kashmiri chili powder. Add paneer cubes and toss to coat evenly. Sprinkle a little water to help the batter stick. Set aside for 5–10 minutes.</li>
		<li>Fry the paneer: Heat oil in a pan. Shallow or deep fry the coated paneer cubes until golden and crisp on all sides. Drain on paper towels and set aside.</li>
		<li>Sauté aromatics: In a wok or pan, heat 1–2 tbsp oil. Add ginger, garlic, green chilies, and the white part of spring onions. Sauté for 30 seconds until fragrant.</li>
		<li>Cook vegetables: Add onions and bell peppers. Stir-fry on high heat for 2–3 minutes until slightly crisp (do not overcook).</li>
		<li>Add sauces: Lower the heat slightly. Add soy sauce, green chili sauce, red chili sauce, ketchup, vinegar, sugar, and black pepper. Mix well and cook for 1 minute.</li>
		<li>Add sauces: Lower the heat slightly. Add soy sauce, green chili sauce, red chili sauce, ketchup, vinegar, sugar, and black pepper. Mix well and cook for 1 minute.</li>
		<li>Thicken the sauce: Stir the cornflour slurry and add it to the pan. Cook until the sauce thickens into a glossy glaze.</li>
		<li>Combine with paneer: Add the fried paneer cubes and green part of spring onions. Toss gently to coat evenly.</li>
	</ol>
 </article>
